# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SPEC-DRIFT SYNCHRONIZATION RULES
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Critical Sync Points

1. **Invoice Field Definitions**
   - Spec Chapter 4 ↔ `invoice.schema.json` ↔ OCR extraction code
   - Field additions require all three updates

2. **Extraction Confidence Thresholds**
   - Spec Chapter 7 ↔ Code constants in OCR service
   - Threshold changes must be documented

3. **HITL Workflow States**
   - Spec Chapter 5 ↔ `review-task.schema.json`
   - State machine changes need both updates

4. **Quality Metrics**
   - Spec Chapter 7 ↔ Monitoring implementation
   - New metrics need spec documentation

## Pre-Change Checklist

Before modifying this specification:

- [ ] Run `make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=arabic`
- [ ] Review `docs/schema/arabic/` for affected schemas
- [ ] Check OCR service implementation impact
- [ ] Verify HITL interface compatibility

## Post-Change Checklist

After modifying this specification:

- [ ] Update `docs/schema/arabic/*.schema.json` if data model changed
- [ ] Update `src/intelligence/ocr/` if extraction changed
- [ ] Run `make audit-spec-drift` to verify synchronization
- [ ] Update `docs/summaries/arabic-ap-summary.md`

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ARABIC-SPECIFIC STANDARDS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Right-to-Left (RTL) Considerations

When documenting Arabic text handling:
- Document text direction requirements explicitly
- Specify field alignment for mixed content
- Note Unicode normalization requirements

## Field Naming for Arabic Content

| Field Type | English Name | Arabic Label |
|------------|--------------|--------------|
| Invoice Number | invoice_number | رقم الفاتورة |
| Amount | amount | المبلغ |
| Date | date | التاريخ |
| Vendor | vendor_name | اسم المورد |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# REQUIREMENT ID CONVENTIONS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

| Category | Prefix | Example |
|----------|--------|---------|
| Extraction | ARA-EXT | ARA-EXT-001 |
| HITL | ARA-HITL | ARA-HITL-001 |
| Quality | ARA-QA | ARA-QA-001 |
| Integration | ARA-INT | ARA-INT-001 |
| OCR | ARA-OCR | ARA-OCR-001 |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# QUALITY THRESHOLDS (Authoritative)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

These thresholds are authoritative - code MUST match:

| Metric | Value | Source |
|--------|-------|--------|
| OCR confidence threshold | ≥ 0.85 | Chapter 7, Section 7.2 |
| Auto-accept threshold | ≥ 0.95 | Chapter 5, Section 5.3 |
| Field extraction rate | ≥ 0.90 | Chapter 7, Section 7.4 |
| Human review rate target | ≤ 0.30 | Chapter 7, Section 7.5 |

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DRIFT DETECTION COMMANDS
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

```bash
# Full audit for arabic domain
make audit-spec-drift-domain DOMAIN=arabic

# Check schema validity
python3 docs/schema/validate.py --domain arabic

# Review source document status
ls -la docs/arabic/machine-readable/
```

